.SH FILES
Default location is \fI$RSVP_HOME\fR or \fI~/.rsvp/\fR:
\(bu \fIconfig.json\fR \(en user configuration (theme, wpm, keybindings).
\(bu \fIlibrary.db\fR \(en SQLite store of books, chapters, and notes.
\(bu \fInotes/\fR \(en on\-disk note storage.
\(bu \fIcache/\fR \(en per\-book parsed\-text cache.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fB\fBRSVP_HOME\fR\fR
Override the data directory (default \fI~/.rsvp\fR).
.TP
\fB\fBRSVP_NEW_UI\fR\fR
Force\-enable the new SettingsScreen (set to \fB1\fR).
.TP
\fB\fBNO_COLOR\fR\fR
Disable ANSI colour in the helper scripts.
.TP
\fB\fBPYTHONIOENCODING\fR\fR
Set to \fButf\-8\fR when reading non\-ASCII books.
.SH EXAMPLES
Launch the TUI at the library view:
    rsvp
Read a book at 450 WPM in focus mode:
    rsvp read ~/books/sapiens.epub \-\-wpm 450 \-\-focus
Import a Markdown file and read it:
    rsvp i ./essay.md && rsvp r ./essay.md
Re\-build the Rust extension in dev mode:
    uv run dev
Run the full quality gate:
    uv run verify
Render and install the man page:
    uv run man \-\-install
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
If a book fails to import, the database is missing, or a keybinding fails to resolve, run \fBuv run doctor\fR \(en the JSON report names the offending file. Exits 0 only on a healthy install.
Exit codes: \fB0\fR success, \fB1\fR generic error, \fB130\fR interrupted (Ctrl\-C).
